  "H_T_Link__c" : "https://help.salesforce.com/HTTrainingCourseDetail?id=a230M000000wsMc",
  "In_person_Duration__c" : "4 days",
  "Lessons_and_topics__c" : "<p><br></p><p><b>Getting Started </b></p><p> • Salesforce B2C Commerce Overview</p><p>• SiteGenesis Overview </p><p>• Site Configuration </p><p><br></p><p><b>UX Studio </b></p><p>• Creating a Workspace </p><p>• Creating a Server Connection </p><p>• B2C Commerce Views</p><p><br></p><p><b>Cartridges</b></p><p>• Cartridge Path </p><p>• Cartridge Types </p><p>• Creating a SiteGenesis Storefront Cartridge </p><p><br></p><p><b>JavaScript Controllers </b></p><p>• Introduction to JavaScript Controllers </p><p>• Creating a JavaScript Controller</p><p>• Script and JavaScript Controller Debugging</p><p><br></p><p><b>ISML </b></p><p>• ISML Tags and Expressions </p><p>• Creating and Accessing Variables </p><p>• Reusing Code in Templates </p><p>• Conditional Statements and Loops </p><p><br></p><p><b>Content Slots </b></p><p>• Creating &amp; Configuring Content Slots </p><p>• Using Content Link Functions </p><p><br></p><p><b>Commerce Cloud Digital Script</b></p><p>• B2C Commerce Script API</p><p>• Resource API and Resource Bundles </p><p><br></p><p><b>Forms Framework </b></p><p>• XML Metadata File </p><p>• ISML Form Template</p><p>• Pipeline / JavaScript Controller Elements</p><p>Custom Objects </p><p><br></p><p><b>Using B2C Commerce Script to Create Custom Object Instances</b></p><p>• Custom Logging </p><p>• Data Binding and Explicit Transactions </p><p>• Data Binding with Forms and Objects </p><p><br></p><p><b>Site Maintenance </b></p><p>• Site and Page Caching </p><p>• Site Performance </p><p>• Code Replication </p><p>• Data Replication</p>",
  "Level__c" : "Intermediate",
  "Name" : "Developing for Salesforce B2C Commerce",
  "Objectives__c" : "<p>• Create cartridges to add reusable functionality to a site. </p><p>• Use JavaScript controllers to add business logic to a site. </p><p>• Create reusable code using ISML templates. </p><p>• Use content slots to improve the appearance and flexibility of a site. </p><p>• Use B2C Commerce Script in ISML templates and script files. </p><p>• Use the Forms Framework to control the validation, rendering, and storing of consumer-entered values. </p><p>• Maintain pipelines if they exist on a site.</p>",
